The forecast calibration relies on ensemble inflation32, which is here expanded to correct the long-term trend and the ensemble spread individually. The recalibrated ensemble (y) comprises the linear trend (xTR), the detrended ensemble mean (xEM), and the ensemble deviation from the ensemble mean (x’EM), while each component is multiplied by their respective correction factor that leads to the optimal calibration under Normal statistics2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
